# KitchCu Security & Observability

Read `docs/KITCHCU-ENGINEERING-STANDARDS.md` §10–11.

## Multi-tenancy

- Every tenant table: `kitchen_id` + query filter in domain layer
- Cache keys include tenant: `menu:{kitchen_id}`, not global
- Admin routes: platform scope only; no owner JWT on admin APIs

## Security (OWASP)

- Pydantic validation on all inputs · SQLAlchemy parameterized queries
- No secrets in code · env vars + `.env.example`
- Mask phone/PII in logs
- Signed URLs for media (when media service active)
- Rate limiting on gateway (implement in S5/S6)

## Auth

- Owner: OTP + JWT Bearer
- Admin: platform JWT via identity
- Future: refresh tokens, RBAC permissions per route

## Observability

- `/health/live` + `/health/ready` on every service (required)
- Structured logs · no PII
- Correlation ID: `ckac_common.observability.CorrelationMiddleware` on gateway; forward `X-Correlation-ID` to services
- Phase 2: OpenTelemetry + Prometheus

## Do not

- Return cross-tenant data in API or cache
- Log OTP, tokens, or full phone numbers
- Bypass gateway for public clients
